<TITLE> Govt pulls executive officials out of magisterial jobs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 30 (bdnews24.com)The government Tuesday started withdrawing executive officials from magisterial jobs in the run-up to the separation of the judiciary from the executive, scheduled to take effect from November 1. Ten magistrates, including the chief metropolitan magistrates for Dhaka, Khulna, Rajshahi and Chittagong, have already been withdrawn. Three of the magistrates have been posted to administrative positions and seven others have been placed with the establishment ministry for posting, according to a circular by the establishment ministry. Chief metropolitan magistrate for Dhaka Tarikul Islam has been made joint secretary of the cabinet division. CMM for Khulna Jamaluddin Ahmed has been made deputy secretary of the Energy and Mineral Resources Division and CMM for Chittagong AKM Shahidur Rahman has been posted to the Power Division as deputy secretary. CMM for Rajshahi Afzal Hossain, Dhaka metropolitan magistrates Abul Bashar Mohammad Abdul Fattah and Golam Rahman Miah, additional CMMs for Dhaka Helal Uddin, Abdus Salam Miah and Matiur Rahman and additional CMM for Chittagong Mafizul Islam have been placed with the establishment ministry following their withdrawal. Two deputy secretaries have also been transferred. Deputy secretary of the agriculture ministry Jagdish Chandra Biswas has been made the deputy controller of insurance and the deputy secretary of the land ministry Sajjad Kabir has been transferred to the information ministry. Earlier, Dhaka metropolitan magistrate Rokanuddowla was made OSD and Khulna metropolitan magistrate Shefina Begum was placed with the establishment ministry. bdnews24.com
